<paragraph id="AC34368AFFD2FFE524C4FE1371830215" blockId="8.[192,1441,257,603]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="9EFFEA98FFD2FFE524C4FE1372020195" bold="true" box="[240,637,386,411]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
Unmounted material (
<figureCitation id="34B02A0FFFD2FFE52614FE1272120195" box="[544,621,386,411]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[192,276,697,719]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,192,672]" captionTargetId="figure-396@7.[192,1440,192,672]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Foldilecanium multisetosus Kondo. A) Colony of various growth stages, with adult females in center of photo. Inset photo showing an adult female with flaky, glassy wax cover. B) Colony of older and heavily sclerotized adult females being tended by Azteca sp. ants. All photos taken after removal of ant cartons." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160595" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5160595/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Adult female in life about 3.0 mm long, 
<quantity id="6B739B6FFFD2FFE52055FE1374C30195" box="[1121,1212,387,411]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
wide, oval, moderately convex. Scale covered by a thin layer of a flaky glassy wax (see inset on 
<figureCitation id="34B02A0FFFD2FFE520A6FE33748E01B5" box="[1170,1265,419,443]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[192,276,697,719]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,192,672]" captionTargetId="figure-396@7.[192,1440,192,672]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Foldilecanium multisetosus Kondo. A) Colony of various growth stages, with adult females in center of photo. Inset photo showing an adult female with flaky, glassy wax cover. B) Colony of older and heavily sclerotized adult females being tended by Azteca sp. ants. All photos taken after removal of ant cartons." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160595" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5160595/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Young adult females (
<figureCitation id="34B02A0FFFD2FFE5251AFE5371F801D5" box="[302,391,451,475]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[192,276,697,719]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,192,672]" captionTargetId="figure-396@7.[192,1440,192,672]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Foldilecanium multisetosus Kondo. A) Colony of various growth stages, with adult females in center of photo. Inset photo showing an adult female with flaky, glassy wax cover. B) Colony of older and heavily sclerotized adult females being tended by Azteca sp. ants. All photos taken after removal of ant cartons." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160595" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5160595/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) sligthly convex, orange to purplish red in color, often with mottlings of a darker color. Older specimens (
<figureCitation id="34B02A0FFFD2FFE525A0FE73719501F5" box="[404,490,483,507]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="7.[192,276,697,719]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,192,672]" captionTargetId="figure-396@7.[192,1440,192,672]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 2. Foldilecanium multisetosus Kondo. A) Colony of various growth stages, with adult females in center of photo. Inset photo showing an adult female with flaky, glassy wax cover. B) Colony of older and heavily sclerotized adult females being tended by Azteca sp. ants. All photos taken after removal of ant cartons." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160595" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5160595/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
) becoming heavily sclerotized, brown in color, with thick and dark color elevated rim around body margins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC34368AFFD2FFE524C4FDB371DB0255" blockId="8.[192,1441,257,603]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="9EFFEA98FFD2FFE524C4FDB372D30235" bold="true" box="[240,684,546,571]" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">
Slide-mounted material (
<figureCitation id="34B02A0FFFD2FFE52679FDB272E30235" box="[589,668,546,571]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="9.[192,276,1793,1815]" captionTargetBox="[237,1440,192,1758]" captionTargetId="figure-14@9.[192,1440,192,1758]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 3. Foldilecanium multisetosus Kondo, adult female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5160597/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="7">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Slide mounted specimens1.8-3.0 mm long, 
<quantity id="6B739B6FFFD2FFE520FEFDB375280235" box="[1226,1367,547,571]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.05" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="2.05" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="1.5">1.5-2.6 mm</quantity>
wide, body oval in shape.
</paragraph>
