<subSubSection id="E4916501FFD0FFE724F4FEB371BB0155" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AC34368AFFD0FFE724F4FEB371BB0155" blockId="10.[192,1440,291,347]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="9EFFEA98FFD0FFE724F4FEB371220135" bold="true" box="[192,349,291,315]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet 
<emphasis id="9EFFEA98FFD0FFE72657FEB373770135" box="[611,776,291,315]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
“ 
<taxonomicName id="6B8B4D09FFD0FFE7265FFEB373770135" authorityName="Kondo. A" authorityYear="2011" box="[619,776,291,315]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Foldilecanium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multisetosus">multisetosus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
” is named after the many (5-7) stigmatic setae of the species. Gender male.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E4916501FFD0FFE724F4FE1373F701B2" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="AC34368AFFD0FFE724F4FE1373F701B2" blockId="10.[192,1441,387,444]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="9EFFEA98FFD0FFE724F4FE13714E0195" bold="true" box="[192,305,387,411]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Biology.</emphasis>
The soft scales were abundant on the twigs of its host and tended by 
<taxonomicName id="6B8B4D09FFD0FFE72059FE1474990195" box="[1133,1254,388,411]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Azteca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="9EFFEA98FFD0FFE72059FE1474C20195" box="[1133,1213,388,411]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Azteca</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
ants inside ant cartons. Colonies were composed of different growth stages.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
